menu "BLE HID host"

    config BLE_DEBUG_LOG
        bool "Enable verbose BLE diagnostic logging"
        default n
        help
            Log all BLE GAP/GATT events, connection state transitions, report
            descriptor discovery, and CCCD subscription results to the in-memory
            ring buffer (readable from the BLE log spoiler in the web UI) and to
            the serial console via ESP_LOGI.

            When disabled blog() is a no-op: no serial output, no ring-buffer
            writes. The BLE log spoiler in the web UI will be empty.

endmenu
